Make smry of model

Source: R/fn_make.R
make_smry_of_mdl.Rd

make_smry_of_mdl() is a Make function that creates a new R object. Specifically, this function implements an algorithm to make smry of model. The function returns Smry of one predr model (a tibble).

make_smry_of_mdl(
  data_tb,
  model_mdl,
  n_folds_1L_int = 10,
  dep_var_nm_1L_chr = "utl_total_w",
  start_1L_chr = NULL,
  tfmn_1L_chr = "NTF",
  predr_var_nm_1L_chr,
  covar_var_nms_chr = NA_character_,
  mdl_type_1L_chr = "OLS_NTF",
  mdl_types_lup = NULL,
  pred_type_1L_chr = NULL
)

Arguments

data_tb

Data (a tibble)
model_mdl

PARAM_DESCRIPTION
n_folds_1L_int

N folds (an integer vector of length one), Default: 10
dep_var_nm_1L_chr

Dep var name (a character vector of length one), Default: 'utl_total_w'
start_1L_chr

Start (a character vector of length one), Default: NULL
tfmn_1L_chr

Time series (a character vector of length one), Default: 'NTF'
predr_var_nm_1L_chr

Predr var name (a character vector of length one)
covar_var_nms_chr

Covar var names (a character vector), Default: 'NA'
mdl_type_1L_chr

Model type (a character vector of length one), Default: 'OLS_NTF'
mdl_types_lup

Model types (a lookup table), Default: NULL
pred_type_1L_chr

Pred type (a character vector of length one), Default: NULL

Value

Smry of one predr model (a tibble)
